En este caso, como usamos un valor de cadena en la consulta , solo se produciría una actualización, incluso con la actualización automática habilitada. Sin embargo, si proporcionamos un objeto Dirección, es posible que sin darnos cuenta activemos múltiples solicitudes mientras configuramos sus propiedades.

Sampling the texture with our external image is done using TEXTURE_UV. INPUT_UV is not suitable in cross-platform applications since V needs to be flipped to cater for the coordinate system differences mentioned before, using a logic that is different for textures based on images and textures used as render targets. trans-unit.source: The general approach to using XQuery to perform queries on non-XML data has been a three step process. In the first step, the data is loaded into a non-XML data model. In the second step, the non-XML data model is serialized as XML and output to XML (text) files. In the final step, an XML tool loads the XML files into a second, XML data model, where the XQueries can be performed. The development cost of implementing this process is often high, and the three step system that results is inefficient because the two data models must be built and maintained separately.

The development cost of implementing this process is often high, and the three step system that results is inefficient because the two data models must be built and maintained separately.

trans-unit.source: The image description. Some image formats, such as GIF and PNG, allow embedding of text or comments into the image data (e.g., for storing copyright information). QImageIOHandler returns the text as one QString, where keys and values are separated by a ':', and keys-value pairs are separated by two newlines ( ).
